news.title: SCR plans to transform vacant properties in Hyderabad into commercial hubs
news.para: Railway authorities invited expressions of interest to utilise empty lands at eight prime locations, including Lallaguda, Mettuguda, Arts College, Alwal, and Uppuguda.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad: PCMC's move to add property tax dues on share certificates draws flak
news.para: PCMC officials said they've also written to the District Deputy Registrar of Cooperative Housing Societies of Pune, with the suggestion that those who've not paid their property tax be disallowed from voting in housing society elections.

news.title: SC upholds Bombay HC's order for CBI probe into Jai Corp's Rs 2,434 crore fraud case
news.para: However, a bench led by Justice JB Pardiwala said that Jai Corp and others are at liberty to seek quashing of the FIR filed by the Economic Offences Branch of CBI, Mumbai, before an appropriate court, which will decide the case uninfluenced by the HC observations.

news.title: Jaipur development body to establish comprehensive data bank of all properties
news.para: The buyers need not apply for the name transfer process as the names of new buyers would be automatically updated in JDA's records, said officials.

news.title: Approval of maps must before building construction: Prayagraj development body
news.para: PDA is holding ‘Manchitra Samadhan Diwas' (Map/Layout Solution Day) every Thursday of the month for building construction in Sangam City.

news.title: Booking for Delhi development body's 828 LIG, EWS flats to start today
news.para: Following the high demand for affordable housing, these flats will be available in addition to the units already part of DDA's ongoing Sabka Ghar Awaas Yojana 2025, stated the authority.

news.title: Lucknow development body to build township in BKT
news.para: The new township is expected to provide housing for at least three lakh people. LDA identified land in 14 villages, including Bhauli, Baurumau, Dhatingra, Goparamau, Lakshmipur and Purwa.

news.title: Existing property owners are also allottees: Gujarat RERA
news.para: The authority ruled in favour of a complainant, ordering a developer to complete the sale deed registration process while recognising the complainant's status as an allottee.

news.title: Civic body can’t cap balcony length citing building bylaws: Karnataka HC
news.para: "The floor area of the balcony shall, however, be taken into consideration while calculating the FAR (floor area ratio), and builders can't claim exemption in respect of this area, as provided under the building bylaws, 2003," Justice NS Sanjay Gowda specified in his order while disposing of a couple of petitions.

news.title: Kolkata: 17-acre plot in New Town worth Rs 800 crore to go for auction
news.para: The plot is in Action Area 1, located between Novotel and the Axis Mall. It is one of the largest parcels that's going for auction in a decade in such a prime area.

news.title: Haryana RERA sends Ninaniya Estates' director to civil jail over unpaid refund
news.para: Ninaniya Estates Limited director Prateek Rao was arrested following an execution petition filed by decree holders seeking the enforcement of Rs 26,07,780 refund order issued by the regulator on Nov 15, 2023.

news.title: Sunac China warns of wider loss for 2024
news.para: In late 2023, Sunac completed a comprehensive overhaul of its $9 billion offshore debt, exchanging its existing debt for a combination of notes, among others.

news.title: Haryana CM announces affordable rental housing for migrants
news.para: Saini stated that the state government aims to provide clean and affordable rental housing to urban migrants, unorganised sector workers and economically weaker sections (EWS) through the Affordable Rental Housing Scheme under Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana (Urban) 2.0.

news.title: Over 38 lakh people added in official app as potential beneficiaries under PMAY-G: Bihar minister
news.para: He made the announcement in the assembly during a discussion on the budget proposal of Rs 16,093 crore of the Rural Development Department (RDD) for the 2025-26 fiscal.

news.title: Canadian home sales fall 9.8% in February 2025: CREA data
news.para: Sales fell 9.8% in February from January, the biggest decline since May 2022, and were down 10.4% on an annual basis.

news.title: Over 7,400 projects completed so far under smart cities mission: Housing minister
news.para: Khattar said more than 7,400 projects have been completed so far in 100 cities under Smart Cities Mission (SCM) and those under progress will be completed. He said if there are any demand till March 31, 2025, that will also be fulfilled.

news.title: Illegal constructions completely stopped in Kolkata: Mayor
news.para: The minister also asked other civic bodies in the state to take similar steps and stop any illegal construction in their respective jurisdictions.

news.title: Tariffs on imported goods may raise cost of building materials in US
news.para: The tariffs are projected to raise the costs that go into building a single-family home in the US by USD 7,500 to USD 10,000, according to the National Association of Home Builders.

news.title: Ajmera Realty to redevelop residential society in Andheri West, Mumbai
news.para: The project, covering a total land area of 2,319 sq meters, will be developed in a single phase in Shastri Nagar, Andheri West, Mumbai.

news.title: Capital values in the top seven cities rise by 128% between 2021 and 2024: Anarock data
news.para: NCR's Sohna Road saw capital values go up by 59 per cent while rental values rose by 47 per cent. Sector-150 in Noida saw capital values appreciate by a whopping 128 per cent while rental values rose by just 66 per cent in the period.
